description:
InstantUplinkAccess: Table recording instantaneous uplink access parameters for a given cell at a specific time.

dateTime: Timestamp of the measurement.
Area_Name: Name of the geographical area where the cell is located.
CellId: Unique identifier for the cell.
Id2:  Duplicate or alternative identifier for the cell (likely redundant).
Id3: Another identifier for the cell or a related entity.
Id4:  Unknown identifier, likely redundant or irrelevant.
vsDataType: Type of data.
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format.
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaTargetBufferEmptyTime: Time (in ms?) until target buffer is empty.
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaDuration: Duration of uplink access (in ms?).
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaInactivityTimer: Inactivity timer for uplink access (in ms?).
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaTargetBufferSize: Size of the target buffer.
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaIntervalTdd: Measurement interval for TDD systems.
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaEnabled: Status of uplink access (true/false).
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaLoadThreshold: Load threshold triggering uplink access control.
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaCellResourceLimit: Cell resource limit for uplink access.
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaSinrThreshold: SINR threshold for uplink access.
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaUePrbLimit: PRB limit for UEs in uplink access.
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaDeactPdcchMargin: PDCCH margin for deactivation.
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaCoscheduleDynamic: Whether co-scheduling is dynamic.
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaDeactTimer: Deactivation timer.
InstantUplinkAccess.instantUplinkAccessId: Unique identifier for this specific uplink access instance.
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaIntervalFdd: Measurement interval for FDD systems.
InstantUplinkAccess.iuaSinrDeactHyst: SINR hysteresis for deactivation.
